 middle. And, therefore, it <EVENT class="STATE" eid="e120">works</EVENT> very well.


 Nationwide, there are about ten thousand patients <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e72">waiting</EVENT> for liver <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e73">transplants</EVENT>
 <TIMEX3 functionInDocument="NONE" quant="EACH" temporalFunction="false" tid="t107" type="SET" value="P1Y">each year</TIMEX3> and only four thousand organs <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e74">become</EVENT> available for <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e75">transplants</EVENT>.
 Secretary Shalala <EVENT class="REPORTING" eid="e76">says</EVENT> UNOS <TIMEX3 anchorTimeID="t95" functionInDocument="NONE" temporalFunction="true" tid="t108" type="DATE" value="1997-10">five months ago</TIMEX3>, or <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e77">gave</EVENT> them <TIMEX3 functionInDocument="NONE" temporalFunction="false" tid="t109" type="DURATION" value="P5M">five months</TIMEX3> to <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e79">develop</EVENT> a new <EVENT class="I_STATE" eid="e111">plan</EVENT> to <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e81">distribute</EVENT> livers which are in the shortest supply.
